create wind. What on earth did you do here?

Girl Relm: I made a magic circle that vibrates the air,
referring to the magic circle written on another page.

Girl Relm: I'm sorry for doing something strange without
permission...

Old Mage: Hahaha... Hahahaha! A child like you can
understand and dismantle a magic circle!?

Old Mage: You are in a realm that many people cannot reach
in their lifetime! I want to recommend you to the Magic

Old Mage: A genius like you shouldn't end up as a road
worker's daughter!

Girl Relm: ...If I enter the Magic Academy, will I be
recognized?

Old Mage: Of course! Everyone in Kanonas, no, everyone in
the Empire will recognize you!
Girl Relm: I wonder if Dad will also recognize me...?

Old Mage: If a human living in the Empire enters the Magic

Girl Relm: I will enter the Magic Academy!

Old Mage: ...I see, you don't have a dream for the Academy,

Old Mage: How about this? You love books, don't you? I have

Old Mage: The blank grimoire created by the founder of

Having a dream. Relm felt that this was something incredibly
dazzling and beautiful. Just thinking about dreams made her
heart burn passionately.

Relm captured a dream as something that would make herself
shine and sparkle, completely different from the purpose of
wanting to be recognized by her father and family. It was
something more precious and should be prioritized above all
else.

Relm decided to stop trembling in her small room and set out
towards her dream. When she told her father about it, his
response was just a single word, I see. Relm once again
understood that she was not needed by her father.

Relm, guided by the old man, decides to take the entrance
exam for the Magic Academy. Despite having only a short
period of exposure to magic, she easily passes the
notoriously difficult exam.

Relm will build a full-fledged career as a magician, not for
anyone else, but for her own dream.

To prove that there is value in dreaming and meaning in
pursuing those dreams.
